<br>
6/20/02:<br>
Other night Dami, Dasi, Alegura, myself and two druids that happened to be in Kael decided to head to the bank and kill some mobs for exp and fun. While we were there a group of SR members came to the bank area and asked that we hold pulls while they pulled a mob from the Tormax area just up past the bank. We obliged and watched what some of the best players on the server do best. We assisted this group in killing the Mob that was singled out of about 30 very large, very red giants. After they were finished they kindly buffed us with Aego. As they were getting ready to leave a Dwarf warrior that was pulling single mobs up past us on the ramp to kill them with his cleric friend had a bad pull and aggroed Noble Helsen. SR helped us to drop him and then headed out. <br>
<br>
Shortly after resuming pulling I accidentally aggroed one of the lvl 55 Drakkel Direwolves and I proceeded to take a nap. I layed there for what I felt was long enough for these 8 dogs to reset at their bind spots(These were leftovers from the SR pull and were late in getting back home to guarding the ice). I then stood up and ran back to the group and got ready to pull another giant. Suddenly I see a couple of these dogs running towards us in their normal pathing (which is messed up). I Feigned death as fast as I could but the mobs continued to rush the rest of the group. This was not gonna be pretty and we all knew it. The Druid immediately started casting Succor and someone else said EVAC! I jumped up immediately and ran to the group. By this time Dami had taken aggro on one or two of the mobs and ran directly to the middle of the bank area. He unselfishly gave his life to save the rest of us from a certain death. Thanks to him we were able to be succored to the EW Zone and proceed to make a speedy CR of our fallen Hero.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the selfless act Dami. I am very happy to stand by you any day in combat. I know very well you have my back bro. (sub/wit=Aerrenn)<br>
